🔐 Security Best Practices
Release unused Elastic IPs to avoid unnecessary costs.
Avoid exposing unnecessary services to the public internet.
Associate EIPs only with properly secured instances.
Use Security Groups to restrict access even when EIP is assigned.
Track and document all public IP usage for governance.

💰 Cost Awareness (Important)

AWS charges for Elastic IPs when:

They are allocated but not attached to a running instance
You exceed free-tier limits

Always release unused Elastic IPs in non-production environments.

